  "description": [
    "TheNews Glie light and the people will firel their own wap A SCRIPPS HOWARD NEWSPAPER 1013 13th St N W Phone District 7777 By Carrier Week 10c By Mail Month 60c Year 720 LOWELL MELLETT Editor HOWARD PARISH Business Manager MR DOOLEY UP TO DATE THE POINT seems to be that the Supreme Court follows the predilection returns NOT THE ANSWER NOW THAT state minimum wage laws for women and chil dren are once more constitutional several legislatures have started work on such measures In some 17 states laws of this character already are in existence and with the constitutional cloud lifted a real effort to enforce them may now be attempted Suchactivity is for the good and should be pushed as fast as possible Such laws can be helpful in raising wage standards in intrastate industries But nothing could be more obvious than that this movement even tho extended to include minimum wages for men workers cannot get very far in industries which sell their products in the national marketsand that includes practically every line of manufacturing and agriculture In the Washington State law which the court upheld we have a very good example of the limitations of state"
